IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION OPERATES A SENIOR LIVING COMMUNITY THAT PROVIDES A FULL COMPLEMENT OF HEALTH SERVICES.
IRS990.Desc: THE MORSELIFE HOUSING CORPORATION'S ASSISTED LIVING AND INDEPENDENT LIVING FACILITIES INCLUDE 326 UNITS, INCLUDING STUDIO, ONE-BEDROOM, AND TWO-BEDROOM APARTMENTS. RESIDENTS HAVE THE OPTION TO ENHANCE THEIR LIVING ARRANGEMENT WITH EXTRA LEVELS OF CARE THAT PROVIDES ADDITIONAL HANDS-ON CARE. SERVICES PROVIDED INCLUDE MEALS, NURSING CARE, RECREATION, AND SOCIAL SERVICES. ALL ASSISTED LIVING RESIDENTS ARE AT RISK FOR LONG-TERM CARE (SKILLED NURSING FACILITY PLACEMENT). THE ASSISTED LIVING ENVIRONMENT (AVERAGE AGE 90+) IS INSTRUMENTAL IN AVOIDING AND/OR DELAYING PLACEMENT IN AN INSTITUTIONAL SETTING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MORSELIFE HOUSING CORPORATION, INC. IS INCLUDED IN THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OF THE MORSELIFE HEALTH SYSTEM, INC. THE CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING FOOTNOTE: THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE HAS DETERMINED THAT THE MEMBERS OF THE GROUP ARE EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES AND ARE QUALIFIED AS TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (THE "CODE"). ACCORDINGLY, THESE COMBINED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS INCLUDE NO PROVISION OR LIABILITY FOR INCOME TAXES.

THE MORSELIFE HOUSING CORPORATION, INC. MAINTAINS ONE NONQUALIFIED EMPLOYEE DEFERRED COMPENSATION PLAN OPEN TO CERTAIN KEY EMPLOYEES UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE 457(B) AND SECTION 457(F) (COLLECTIVELY, THE 457 PLANS). THE 457 PLANS PROVIDE, AMONG OTHER THINGS, FOR VOLUNTARY CONTRIBUTIONS TO BE MADE BY ELIGIBLE PARTICIPANTS. THESE FUNDS REMAIN THE PROPERTY OF MORSELIFE HEALTH SYSTEM, INC. AND SUBSIDIARIES. MORSELIFE HEALTH SYSTEM, INC. AND SUBSIDIARIES HAVE A FIDUCIARY DUTY OF ACCOUNTABILITY FOR THESE FUNDS. THE MORSELIFE HOUSING CORPORATION, INC. SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AS OF JANUARY 1, 2019, THE AGENCY ENTERED INTO A MANAGEMENT AGREEMENT ("AGREEMENT") WITH AMPLIFII MANAGEMENT, LLC ("AMPLIFII"), AN UNRELATED, FOR-PROFIT ENTITY, TO PROVIDE SPECIFICALLY DESCRIBED CONSULTING SERVICES WHICH ENCOMPASS RECOMMENDATIONS, SUPPORT, GUIDANCE AND OVERSIGHT WITH RESPECT TO THE OVERALL BUSINESS OPERATIONS AND DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES OF THE AGENCY THAT ARE ALSO CLOSELY ALINED WITH AMPLIFII'S CONSULTING SERVICES AS PROVIDED TO OTHER RELATED HEALTH CARE FACILITIES. THE INITIAL TERM OF THE AGREEMENT IS FOR A PERIOD OF FIVE (5) YEARS AND MAY BE EXTENDED FOR AN ADDITIONAL PERIOD OF FIVE (5) YEARS AS AGREED. THE AGREEMENT PROVIDES FOR THE PAYMENT OF CONSULTING FEES TO AMPLIFII BASED ON A DEFINED PERCENTAGE OF THE AGENCY'S ADJUSTED GROSS REVENUES. AMPLIFII IS SOLELY RESPONSIBLE FOR ALL ITS OPERATING EXPENSES INCURRED IN PROVIDNG THE CONSUTLING SERVICES DEFIND IN THE AGREEMENT WITH THE AGENCY, WITHOUT PROVISION FOR REIMBURSEMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMMITTEE, COMPOSED OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FROM EACH OF THE MORSELIFE RELATED ORGANIZATIONS AND THE SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT OF FINANCE, IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE REVIEW OF THE FORM 990.
